  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 220°C. Slice or grate the mushrooms, then put them onto a baking tray with the sesame oil, soy sauce and a big pinch of ground white pepper. Mix well to coat and roast for 25 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, finely chop the garlic then peel and finely chop the ginger. Heat a splash of olive oil in a large lidded saucepan set over a medium heat and add the garlic and ginger. Cook for 5 mins. Add the tomato purée and turmeric and cook for 2 mins until thickened. Add the rice, chopped tomatoes and stock, stir and pop a lid on. Cook for 30 mins until the rice is cooked but still a bit soupy. Throw in your spinach and give it a mix once it's looking ready."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Deseed and finely chop the chilli. Finely chop the spring onions and pick the coriander. Serve the rice in bowls topped with the mushrooms, spring onions, coriander and chilli."
    }
  ],
